# .mailmap — consolidate scattered git commit identities
#
# Format:
#   <canonical-name> <canonical-email> <commit-name> <commit-email>
#   <canonical-name> <canonical-email> <commit-email>
#
# Git natively honors this: `git log --use-mailmap`, `git shortlog`,
# and GitHub's contributor graph all read it. No history rewrite needed.
#
# Add yourself here if your commits have been going under multiple
# name/email combos and you want them consolidated.

